Step 1: Identify the quick assets at the end of the reporting period. Quick assets include:
 • Cash on Hand = 4,560,423.24
 • Bank Deposits = 3,655,000.00
 • Interest Receivable = 10,051.66
 • Accounts Receivable = 1,133,414.13

Step 2: Sum these quick assets:
 4,560,423.24 + 3,655,000.00 = 8,215,423.24  
 8,215,423.24 + 10,051.66 = 8,225,474.90  
 8,225,474.90 + 1,133,414.13 = 9,358,889.03

Step 3: Identify the current liabilities at the end of the reporting period:
 Total Current Liabilities = 1,124,588.25

Step 4: Calculate the Quick Ratio:
 Quick Ratio = (Quick Assets) / (Current Liabilities)  
 Quick Ratio = 9,358,889.03 / 1,124,588.25  
 Quick Ratio ≈ 8.32

Thus, the answer is:
